adia","remark":"Port Plaquemine updated USD - 21.500"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-20T15:20:59.397","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"Voyage was fixed with a call in S. Africa but we were able to avoid a laden bunker stop due proper prior planning which saved $15k in berth and pilot fees. The Dow terminal in Plaquemine created a hiccup as they presented a max draft of 39\u2019 but once alongside vessel soundings showed a depth of only 36\u2019. We leaned on Alcoa to advise how they wanted to proceed and ultimately were shifted to Shintec for balance cargo, tugs and pilots rebilled. Otherwise voyage completed without issue. 6 days at Lake Charles and 4 in the river lead to a $103k demurrage claim. The main reason for TCE improvement is the bunker adjustment clause which compensates us $1,280 for every dollar increase in VLSFO price above $315/MT. The Platts price on B/L date was $605.5 which leads to additional revenue of $372k."},{"modifiedDate":"2021-11-17T19:16:24.06","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Bunker adjustment higher than expected"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-10-12T17:17:21.403","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"routing adjusted via Cape vs Panama Canal which adds 4 days \u002B 400 MT reduction in cargo due restriction at Plaquemine"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-10-11T21:10:56.02","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"TCE increase due bunker planning allowing for direct passage to Kwinana from USG"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}